<div id="pf111e" class="pf w1f h126" data-page-no="111e"><div class="pc pc111e w1f h126"><div class="t m1648 x59 h4 y2334 ff4 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">SABBATH SCHOOL LESSON QUARTERLY </div><div class="t m5 x9d h4 y2334 ff4 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">î˜‰</div><div class="t m1532 xb6 h15 y2334 ff4 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">7 </div><div class="t m260 x2d h67 y2080 ff6 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">The Narrative </div><div class="t m988 x5d h15 y62a ff4 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">1. </div><div class="t mf25 x4e h15 y69a ff4 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">How did Paul open his address to those seeking </div><div class="t m83b x27 h15 y1eee ff4 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">for his life? What helped to gain their hearing? Acts </div><div class="t mdb x27 h15 yf91 ff4 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">22:1, 2. Note 1. </div><div class="t m127 x48 h15 y5de ff4 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">2. </div><div class="t m44c x4e h15 y62d ff4 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">What did Paul say of his early life and training? </div><div class="t mdb7 x27 h15 y1990 ff4 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">What of his former well-known attitude toward Chris-</div><div class="t md04 x27 h15 y1849 ff4 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">tianity? Verses 3-5. Note 2. </div><div class="t m2b6 x48 h15 y18b3 ff4 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">3. </div><div class="t mae4 x4e h15 y179a ff4 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">What experience had changed his life? Verses </div><div class="t m37c x27 h15 y20f ff4 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">6-9. Note 3. </div><div class="t ma2 x48 h15 y1894 ff4 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">4. </div><div class="t m136b x4e h15 y1894 ff4 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">What was Paul&apos;s first question after recognizing </div><div class="t m28f x27 h15 y1a81 ff4 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">that Jesus was Lord? What was the Lord&apos;s reply? </div><div class="t m204f x27 h15 y1e13 ff4 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Verse 10. </div><div class="t m1cd x48 h15 y1dc9 ff4 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">5. </div><div class="t m5f1 x60 h15 y17ce ff4 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">In what condition did the youthful, active Saul, or </div><div class="t m10fd x11 h15 y173e